            <scopecontent id="aspace_a5d56492c6cbf3b1fd841e18e42589a3">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This accession includes correspondence, labor agreements, invoices, insurance contracts, and other financial documents relating to the operations of various ships, primarily employed in the guano trade, owned by Richard F. C. Hartley of Saco, Maine. Hartley's ships called at ports in North and South America, Europe, and Asia. Also included are shipping documents relating to trade through San Francisco and New Orleans.</p>
            </scopecontent>
